William Petty

Bill Petty, M. R. William Petty



Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, Exactech, Inc.




Gainesville, FL




Find other people named William Petty




General Info


Sanitary Paper Product Manufacturing



Add Tags— eg, Finance, Business2Business...



William Petty, M.D.
Chairman, Chief Executive Officer
 R. William Petty, M.D., chairman and CEO of Exactech, co-founded the company with the goal of developing a medical company committed to cost-effective, high quality medical care. Petty is professor and chairman of the Department of Orthopaedic Surgery at the University of Florida College of Medicine and has continuing extensive experience in surgical joint reconstruction. Petty is a member of the executive committee of the University of Florida College of Medicine and the hospital board of Shands Hospital, Gainesville, Fla. In addition, he is an examiner for the American Board of Orthopaedic Surgery, is on the Orthopaedic Residency Review Committee of the American Medical Association and is a former member of both the editorial board of the Journal of Bone and Joint Surgery and the executive board of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons. He holds the Kappa Delta Award, the highest recognition given to orthopaedic surgeons for research. The most notable work in his extensive bibliography is “Total Joint Replacement”, a comprehensive book published by W.B. Saunders in 1991. Petty received his Bachelor of Science, Master of Science and Medical Doctorate from the University of Arkansas. He completed his residency in orthopaedic surgery at the Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minn.
