Item Description: Clarendon Press, Oxford, first edition, 1971, 1971. Cloth, 4to, xiii, 103 pp, plates. An excellent bibliography of the man described as "the father of modern economics" but who "also appears as cabin boy on an English merchantman, as pedlar of sham jewellery in France, as naval cadet, as medical student in the Netherlands and in Paris, as reader of music at Gresham College, as Professor of Anatomy at Oxford, as Fellow of the Royal Society, as educationist, inventor, Latin versifier, and ship builder, as physician to Cromwell's army in Ireland, as surveyor and cartographer of Ireland, and in the midst of all this as a man becoming ever more involved in administration, finance and politics." - Preface. The bibliography appends Aubrey's and Evelyn's accounts of Petty, and Aubrey's account of Graunt. Fine in a dustwrapper which is slightly used, sunned around the spine and the top inch of the rear panel, and somewhat torn near the head of the spine.  Bookseller Inventory # ABE-21566

